      "body": "Approach ACK.\n\nThis PR seems like an improvement, fixing file write/ close failure handling and adding coverage for a file write failure scenario that wasn't previously tested. I think `RLIMIT_FSIZE` is a nice way to exercise a real mid-write failure here. Alternatives like `/dev/full`, permission changes, or mocked writers would either test a less realistic path or require more plumbing.",
